      "module_path": "track::composition_root",
      "docs": "Composition root for the track command family. Unit struct: no adapter dependencies injected at construction; all port adapters are wired inline per-method. IN-12/AC-17: the former `fixpoint_resolve` method (which directly constructed and invoked FixpointResolveInteractor, then formatted the result) is removed; the composition root no longer owns any part of the fixpoint-resolve invoke/render path. Orchestration for `sotp track fixpoint-resolve` (repo discovery, base_branch resolution, dry-gate + review + ref-verify gate invocation, FixpointResolveService::resolve invocation) now lives in usecase::fixpoint_resolve_driver::FixpointResolveDriverInteractor (ADR 1328 D4: application orchestration belongs in usecase, not composition or an infrastructure SecondaryAdapter); the four infrastructure::track::fixpoint_resolve_driver adapters it is constructed from each perform only a single narrow I/O concern (ADR 1328 D7: port-impl adapters belong in libs/infrastructure). Render lives in cli_driver::track::TrackDriver. `apps/cli` now dispatches via `TrackCompositionRoot::track_driver().handle(TrackInput::FixpointResolve { .. })` instead of calling this composition root directly.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/branch-strategy-config-driven-2026-06-30/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-05" },
        { "file": "track/items/branch-strategy-config-driven-2026-06-30/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-12" },
        { "file": "track/items/branch-strategy-config-driven-2026-06-30/spec.json", "anchor": "AC-17" }
      ],
      "informal_grounds": []
    },
    "FixpointResolveInput": {
      "action": "delete",
      "role": { "Dto": {} },
      "kind": {
        "kind": "struct",
        "shape": {
          "kind": "plain",
          "fields": [
            { "name": "track_id", "ty": "String" },
            { "name": "current_branch", "ty": "String" },
            { "name": "items_dir", "ty": "std::path::PathBuf" }
          ],
          "has_stripped_fields": false
        }
      },
      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "track::fixpoint_resolve",
      "docs": "Superseded by usecase::fixpoint_resolve_driver::FixpointResolveDriverInput (IN-12): `apps/cli` now routes `sotp track fixpoint-resolve` through TrackCompositionRoot::track_driver().handle(TrackInput::FixpointResolve) instead of calling TrackCompositionRoot::fixpoint_resolve(FixpointResolveInput) directly, per no-backward-compat.md (no permanent parallel entrypoint retained). Role note: this entry's role (Dto) is not R1-legal for cli_composition (R1: Dto is forbidden in cli_composition) -- that placement was itself part of the layer violation IN-12 corrects; recorded here for audit-trail accuracy of the removed item, not as an endorsed placement. The former method's wiring, invoke, and render responsibilities are now split across three layers per ADR 1328 D2/D3/D4: the four fine-grained infrastructure::track::fixpoint_resolve_driver adapters (FsFixpointWorkspaceContextAdapter / FsDryCheckConfigLoaderAdapter / FsFixpointDryGateFactoryAdapter / FsFixpointGateStateFactoryAdapter, each implementing one usecase secondary port; R1: SecondaryAdapter is infrastructure-only) perform only narrow I/O concerns and do not invoke FixpointResolveService; the actual orchestration and FixpointResolveService::resolve invocation live in usecase::fixpoint_resolve_driver::FixpointResolveDriverInteractor (ADR 1328 D4: application orchestration belongs in usecase, not composition or an infrastructure SecondaryAdapter -- an earlier draft that pushed this invocation into a single infrastructure adapter was flagged as a D4 violation, 2026-07-02 plan-artifacts final-review P1 finding, and corrected here); TrackCompositionRoot::track_driver() only constructs and injects the four adapters plus the interactor built from them (wire-only, ADR 1328 D2) and never invokes FixpointResolveDriverService itself. This differs from the pre-existing DryDriverAdapter / TrackServiceImpl (both genuinely pub, both out of this track's IN/AC scope, both structurally coupled to their respective CompositionRoot -- DryDriverAdapter holds DryCompositionRoot + DryFixRunnerCompositionRoot fields and delegates to their methods, TrackServiceImpl calls TrackCompositionRoot::new().track_*() per method -- so neither is relocatable to infrastructure without further restructuring; left as an out-of-scope pre-existing gap, not a pattern to replicate here). The four fixpoint-resolve adapters have no such composition-root dependency (their wiring logic uses only domain / usecase / infrastructure types), so they follow the D7 default placement.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/branch-strategy-config-driven-2026-06-30/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-12" },
        { "file": "track/items/branch-strategy-config-driven-2026-06-30/spec.json", "anchor": "AC-17" }
      ],
      "informal_grounds": []
    },
